HARDWARE
1. Computer (I used a Mac but this should also work on Windows and Linux)
2. Microsoft Kinect

SOFTWARE
1. Install Processing
processing.org/download/
2. Download Processing libraries
-SimpleOpenNI:
code.google.com/p/simple-openni/
-FullScreen:
www.superduper.org/processing/fullscreen_api/
3. Follow the directions to use Processing code in Eclipse
processing.org/learning/eclipse/
4. Download the SWT Library for Eclipse
www.eclipse.org/swt
5. Follow the directions to use SWT in Eclipse
www.eclipse.org/swt/eclipse.php

Now the code should work.

